         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286"><!-- p1l1-r23 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Hd1e108">Rubrica 23</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De puritate animi et cogitatione atque voluntate peccati</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e114">
               De purita<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>te 
               animi et cogitatione atque uoluntate 
               <lb ed="#O"/>peccati. Rubrica. 23
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e118">SAlomon in prouer. capitulo 4</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e127">Omni 
               custodia sua tuum cor quia 
               <lb ed="#O"/>ex ipso uita procedit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e133">
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e132">capitulo 15.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e137">abho<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>minatio 
               domini cogitationes male.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e144"> /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e143"></ref><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e146">
               <lb ed="#O"/>meum purus sum a peccato</quote>
               <!--only this last sentence included in manuscript, attached to last paragraph-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e152">
               <!--line bumps down-->
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e155">Phylon siue filemon: li. sapiente. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e156">
               Peruerse cogitationes separant a deo</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e162">
               
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e167">Math. in euan. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e166">Omnis qui viderit mulierem ad
        concupiscendum eam: iam mechatus est eam in corde suo.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e172">
               
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e176">/ Si oculus tuus dexter scandalizauerit te: <!--39.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="8-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  erue eum et proiice abs te: expedit enim tibi: vt <!--Proiice or Proijce-->
        pereat vnum membrorum tuorum quam totum corpus
        tuum mittatur in gehennam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e193"> ¶
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e198">10. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e195">Estote 
               prudentes sicut serpentes: et simplices sicit columbae.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e201">
               
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e210">Mattheus in euangel. c. 7.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e205">Abintus de 
               corde hominum cogitationes male procedunt: 
               adulteria: fornicationes: homicidia: surta: 
               auaritia: nequitie: dolus: impudicitia: inuidia: 
               oculus: malus: blasphemina: superbia: stultitia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e218">
               
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e229">10. c.</ref>  <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e222">Paruulorum est regnum dei. Quisquis
        non receperit regnum dei velut paruulus: non 
               intrabit in illud.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e230">
               
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e243">Lucas in euangel. c. vi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e234">Bonus homo de bono
        thesauro cordis sui profert bonum: malus homo de
        malo thesauro cordis sui profert malum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-d1e242">
               
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Rd1e257">Iacobus apostolus epistola vnica. c. 1.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de6286-Qd1e246">Unusquisque
        tentatur a concupiscentia sua abstractus et illectus
        deinde concupiscentia cum conceperit parit 
               peccatum. Peccatum vero cum consummatum fuerit 
               generat mortem.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
